 flux variability. ULX-1 is one of the most\nluminous ULXs known, since only 10% of the ULXs exceed a luminosity of\n$\\sim$5$\\times$10$^{40}$ erg s$^{-1}$, but despite its high flux variability we\nfound only weak spectral variability. We classify it as in a hard ultraluminous\nregime of super-Eddington accretion. ULX-2 and ULX-3 are less luminous but also\nvariable in flux and possibly also in spectral shape. We classify them as in\nbetween the hard and the soft ultraluminous regimes. ULX-3 is a transient\nsource: by applying a Lomb-Scargle algorithm we derive a periodicity of $\\sim$\n126 d, which could be associated with an orbital or super-orbital origin.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 22 Feb 2022 20:23:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
