{"id":"2202.11298","submitter":"Iasson Karafyllis","authors":"Iasson Karafyllis, Pierdomenico Pepe, Antoine Chaillet and Yuan Wang","title":"Is Global Asymptotic Stability Necessarily Uniform for Time-Delay\n  Systems?","comments":"25 pages","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.OC cs.SY eess.SY math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For time-invariant finite-dimensional systems, it is known that global\nasymptotic stability (GAS) is equivalent to uniform global asymptotic stability\n(UGAS), in which the decay rate and transient overshoot of solutions are\nrequested to be uniform on bounded sets of initial states. This paper\ninvestigates this relationship for time-invariant delay systems. We show that\nUGAS and GAS are equivalent for this class of systems under the assumption of\nrobust forward completeness, i.e. under the assumption that the reachable set\nfrom any bounded set of initial states on any finite time horizon is bounded.\nWe also show that, if the state space is a space in a particular family of\nSobolev or Holder spaces, then GAS is equivalent to UGAS and that robust\nforward completeness holds. Based on these equivalences, we provide a novel\nLyapunov characterization of GAS (and UGAS) in the aforementioned spaces.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Feb 2022 04:02:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 16 Mar 2022 09:45:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-17"}
